	-----
	USAGE
	-----


To use the assembler (outputs a file ./out.bin):
	cc asm.c -o asm
	./asm file.s

	Option -s outputs each assembled shader to a file (_shader0, _shader1, ...)
	Option -v prints unused label warnings


To use the VM (GLFW, GL 3.1+ - Linux, BSD, likely MacOS):
	cc vm.c -o vm -lGL -lglfw -lm
	./vm out.bin


For example programs see /demos/ - hand-written assembly I used while testing.
